parameters: An Cosán has retained its unique language and culture
despite being part, for a long time, of the Zalivian empire.
An Cosán currently has a good relationship with basically
all of its neighbours except Staparia, keeping to itself and
using diplomacy instead of violence to get its way.
"A Brief History of the Pumllewodic Peoples"
The Pumllewodic are a hybrid people descended from native
Animatan peoples from what are now Trefor and An Cosan and
Sharastran settlers from what are now Sinsu and Taeguk.
Due to the settlement by Sharastran peoples the Pumllewodic
have often had closer relationships with the East than with
the rest of Animata. Culturally they are greatly influenced
through trade with and diplomatic ties to Sharastran
countries. For several centuries the Pumllewodic were
tributaries of a Sinsic Empire. Nevertheless the Sharastran
settlers took on the native languages of the Animatan
The land of the Pumllewodic is known as Sỳian in Treforic
and Saein in An Chosain. Etymology tracks it to Early Tae,
making it one of the few non Animatan words surviving from
Early Pumllewodic. Indeed, the Tae people still refer to the
Pumllewodic lands as "서부 거주지". The original definition
was "the Occident" since at the time these were the
westernmost lands known to the Tae.
While for a long time the name "Pumllewodic" was almost
universally used, modern scholars argue that the names
"Sỳianig" in Treforic and "Saeinach" in An Chosain, which
for a long time have been used almost exclusively in poetic
According to mythology the first Tae settlers were led by
two siblings named Cosan and Trefi. While the scholarly
sister Trefi kept the ties to her old home alive the
adventurous brother Cosan wanted to escape his past.
Thus Cosan left the first settlement to move further north.

Detective Neeson let out a long sigh as he opened the case
report. It was going to be one of those days.
Life in An Cosán's Seirbheis Speisealta, or Special Service,
was nowhere near as exciting as he had imagined when he
signed up all those years ago. In fact, he had found it to
be almost as tedious and bureaucratic as every other
Still, there was a job to be done and he intended to do it.
Neeson began to examine each of the photos in the file,
struggling to keep his eyes open as he did so. Only the
heavy concentration of caffeine and nicotine pulsing through
his veins kept him going. He didn't bother much with sleep
"What kind of feckin name is 'The Dogs'?" he muttered to
himself. It didn't sound to him much like a deadly militant
group. Certainly not one that should be occupying his desk
at the Seirbheis. It wasn't until he turned to the last
photo that he realised just how wrong he was...

events.name: Space Dogs of An Cosán Ch 1

parameters: Domhnall Starkiller landed his ship on the outer rim world
of An Cosán. He clutched his laser saber, the preferred
weapon of a Rauist Knight such as himself, as he disembarked
the ship - this wasn't going to be an easy trade
He walked quickly from the landing pad in the spaceport of
Roinnteia. This place was notorious, nowhere else in the
galaxy would you find such a hive of scum and villainy.
As he sat down for protracted fish tariff discussions with
the Kogojus - a smuggling cartel of slug-like creatures - he
was careful to avoid any public displays of affection.
Kogojin culture prohibited such things, even as they
profited from the traffic of slaves and death sticks.
The Kogoju gang were led by an enigmatic figure known only
as 'Fulc'. Starkiller never dealt with Fulc directly, just
as the Kogojus could never speak directly with his employers
at the HUFMA council. This tended to slow things down but
Starkiller could see no way around it.
"This is the way..." he sighed to himself.
